-- Deutsche Telekom Agrees to Increase Wages at Unit by 6.5 Percent
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-05-07T17:52:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/deutsche-telekom-agrees-to-increase-wages-at-unit-by-6-5-percent.html
Deutsche Telekom AG (DTE)  has reached an
agreement with the Ver.di union to increase the wages of
employees at its Telekom Deutschland unit by 6.5 percent over
two years, the union said.  The accord, which must still be approved by the union’s
salary commission in a Berlin meeting tomorrow, affects 50,000
workers, Ver.di said in an e-mailed statement.  Ver.di added that negotiations with Deutsche Telekoom’s T-
Systems unit workers over wages will resume May 15. Deutsche
Telekom confirmed the agreement with Ver.di in a separate
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
